image.altText: Mitch Marsh clenches his fists and yells in delight as Zak Crawley swings his bat in frustration

items.synopsis: Australia's fast bowlers do their jobs at Headingley but captain Ben Stokes holds the key as England closes in on 251 to win to stay alive in the Ashes. Follow live.

title.children: England has upper hand at lunch despite inroads by Australia's pacemen in third Test

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Four wickets in the session is great for Australia, but England is still well in front in this game, especially with this pair at the crease. Harry Brook is still playing some weird half-hearted shots that would make his childhood coach wince, but he's also clattering the ball to the boundary with startling regularity. And Ben Stokes elevating himself up the order may be the most Alpha move I've seen on a cricket field in some time. After a few Tests of being underwhelmed by so-called Bazball, this is the sort of move I can get behind. He's Freddy Krueger and a fourth-innings run chase at Headingley is definitely Australia's nightmare.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: LUNCH: England 4-153 (Brook 40, Stokes 7)

props.alt: ENgland batters Ben Stokes and Harry Brook run between the wickets in an Ashes Test.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Just sheer pace from Mitch Starc, getting through Moeen Ali's defences. A terrific ball, Moeen tried to drive and just got a slight edge and the ball flew into the stumps. Leg stump ended up tumbling towards the keeper. Starc, meanwhile, looked quite uncomfortable to be honest.
